NPO, People Against Race Classification, has brought a petition to Parliament to scrap the term 'coloured' from South Africa’s legislation. Monique Mortlock has more. #eNCA Courtesy #DStv403  CAPE TOWN - For some, the term 'Coloured' is simply a form of identification, but for others, it is a matter of national importance. READ: Khoisan seek better recognition The non-profit organisation, People Against Race Classification, has brought a petition to Parliament to scrap the term 'Coloured' from South Africa’s legislation. Watch the video above for more details on this story. 